      "role": "user",
      "content": "I mean, you're definitely pointing out the issues with the veto, but some people would argue that the veto and that specific structure are the only reason we even have a global forum to talk in the first place. Like, if you removed the power of the biggest players, wouldn't the whole thing just collapse or be ignored by everyone? Is there any historical argument for why this \"flawed\" system is actually better than the alternatives, or is the whole thing just fundamentally broken?",
