      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The UN's structure, including the veto power, was a compromise between the great powers of the time, and it has allowed the organization to survive and thrive despite its flaws. The alternative, a more centralized and authoritarian global government, would have been even more disastrous, as it would have concentrated too much power in the hands of a few individuals or groups. The UN's system, imperfect as it is, has provided a framework for international cooperation and collective action that has prevented even more catastrophic conflicts, such as a unified European response to the Soviet invasion of Poland in 1939.",
      "source": "target",
